                                <p>A hosting control panel is a tool that helps manage your hosting account and is
                                    especially useful for non-tech savvy users.</p>
                                <p>Currently, we offer two control panel options:<br>1) <a
                                        href="/support/knowledgebase/subcategory/29/cpanel-questions/"
                                        target="_blank">cPanel</a>/<a
                                        href="/support/knowledgebase/subcategory/30/whm-questions/"
                                        target="_blank">WHM</a> - available only with the operating systems CentOS or
                                    CloudLinux OS.</p>
                                <p>2) Interworx - available only with the operating system CentOS. Please note that only
                                    User-Responsible Server Management applies.</p>
                                <p class="gb-mb-0">Price Comparison:</p>
                                <table class="gb-mb-3">
                                    <tbody>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td class="gb-pr-3 gb-pb-1">Interworx (unlimited accounts)</td>
                                            <td class="gb-pb-1">$18.00/month</td>
                                        </tr>
                                        <tr>
                                            <td class="gb-pr-3 gb-pb-1">cPanel Solo (1 account)</td>
                                            <td class="gb-pb-1">$13.88/month</td>
                                        </tr>
                                    </tbody>
                                </table>
                                <p class="gb-mb-0"><a
                                        href="/support/knowledgebase/article.aspx/10246/2252/difference-between-cpanel-and-interworx/"
                                        target="_blank">Learn more about available control panel options →</a></p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <footer></footer>
                    </div>
                    <div class="question">
                        <header>
                            <div class="question__header"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i> <span
                                    class="question__title">
                                    How many websites can I host on a Dedicated Server?
                                </span></div>
                        </header>
                        <div style="display:none;">
                            <div class="question__answer">As many as you like. Although Namecheap does not set any
                                limits on the number of websites you can host, this number depends on a few factors:
                                1) the amount of resources provided with your server and the technologies you use,
                                2) your bandwidth requirements and
                                3) if you have an HTML-designed website or a CMS-based website. Due to the static nature
                                of an HTML-designed website, you can host more websites. With CMS-based websites, you
                                can host fewer websites due to an increase in RAM and CPU processing.</div>
                        </div>
                        <footer></footer>
                    </div>
                    <div class="question">
                        <header>
                            <div class="question__header"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i> <span
                                    class="question__title">
                                    How do I get started with my Dedicated Server setup? Is there any fee for this?
                                </span></div>
                        </header>
                        <div style="display:none;">
                            <div class="question__answer">There is no additional setup fee for hosting Dedicated
                                Servers. Once you’ve bought your Dedicated Server, our Risk Management specialists check
                                your order and forward it along to our Tech Team. Here, they set up a server with the
                                Linux-based operating system (OS) such as CentOS, Ubuntu, Debian or CloudLinux, as well
                                as other addons of your choice. From there, you’ll receive a Welcome Email with your
                                access details and additional instructions. On average, the dedicated server setup
                                process takes less than 4 hours to complete. The exception is for Dedicated Server
                                customers who choose Complete Server Management, which may take longer. If this is the
                                case, our 24/7 Support Team will personally reach out to you.</div>
                        </div>
                        <footer></footer>
                    </div>
                    <div class="question">
                        <header>
                            <div class="question__header"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i> <span
                                    class="question__title">
                                    What are the main differences between the three Server Management options?
                                </span></div>
                        </header>
                        <div style="display:none;">
                            <div class="question__answer">
                                <p class="gb-mb-0">1. User-Responsible<br>
                                    Where you manage and configure your server on your own. This is the default Server
                                    Management choice.</p>
                                <p class="gb-mb-0">2. Basic<br>
                                    Where core services are monitored by Namecheap with a proactive response if there’s
                                    unexpected server failure. Only works with CloudLinux or CentOS and with cPanel
                                    already installed.</p>
                                <p>3. Complete<br>
                                    Where Namecheap runs and manages everything for you. Here, all technical issues are
                                    maintained by our technical experts, letting you focus on your online business.
                                    We’ll take care of your server’s settings, including firewall configurations, PHP
                                    handling, service interruptions with root cause analysis, and more.
                                    Weekly backups to a separate backup server are also offered (up to 200 GB worth of
                                    storage).</p>
                                <p>CentOS or CloudLinux with cPanel is required for Basic and Complete Managements.
                                    Complete Management only applies to servers with two or more disks.</p>
                                <p class="gb-mb-0"><a
                                        href="/support/knowledgebase/article.aspx/9213/2188/what-dedicated-server-management-options-do-you-provide/"
                                        target="_blank">Learn more about your Server Management options →</a></p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <footer></footer>
                    </div>
                    <div class="question">
                        <header>
                            <div class="question__header"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i> <span
                                    class="question__title">
                                    Can I set up a private network/VLAN for my Dedicated Server?
                                </span></div>
                        </header>
                        <div style="display:none;">
                            <div class="question__answer">Due to technical restrictions, a <a
                                    href="/support/knowledgebase/article.aspx/10221/2188/private-network-on-dedicated-servers/"
                                    target="_blank">virtual local area network (VLAN)</a> cannot be set up or installed
                                by you.
                                Please get in touch with our Tech Support Team by <a
                                    href="https://support.namecheap.com/index.php?/Tickets/Submit"
                                    target="_blank">submitting a ticket</a> to Hosting (VPS and Dedicated Servers).
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <footer></footer>
                    </div>
                    <div class="question">
                        <header>
                            <div class="question__header"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i> <span
                                    class="question__title">
                                    What is a CXS License?
                                </span></div>
                        </header>
                        <div style="display:none;">
                            <div class="question__answer">A CXS is a tool that performs active scanning of files as they
                                are uploaded to the server. It can detect suspicious files found on the server, as well
                                as prevent most (but not all) exploits from being uploaded or run on the server.
                                Additionally, CXS allows you to perform on-demand scanning of files, directories, and
                                user accounts to detect suspicious exploits, viruses, and resources. CXS license is
                                installed for free for VPS Quasar and Dedicated plans with the Complete Management.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <footer></footer>
                    </div>
                    <div class="question">
                        <header>
                            <div class="question__header"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i> <span
                                    class="question__title">
                                    Where is my Dedicated Server located?
                                </span></div>
                        </header>
                        <div style="display:none;">
                            <div class="question__answer">All Dedicated Servers from Namecheap are located in the USA
                                (PhoenixNAP datacenter, TX, US). Find out more about our <a
                                    href="/support/knowledgebase/article.aspx/136/22/where-are-your-datacenters-located/"
                                    target="_blank">Dedicated Servers in the USA</a>.</div>
                        </div>
                        <footer></footer>
                    </div>
                    <div class="question">
                        <header>
                            <div class="question__header"><i class="fa fa-angle-down"></i> <span
                                    class="question__title">
                                    Which Dedicated Server should I choose?
                                </span></div>
                        </header>
                        <div style="display:none;">
                            <div class="question__answer">
                                <p>We offer a wide range of Dedicated Servers with different configurations that are
                                    suitable for everyone, depending on how much physical resources you need.</p>
                                <p>If you are not sure what configuration to choose, we recommend collecting the system
                                    requirements for the software you plan to host and estimating the budget from there.
                                    You can start with Namecheap’s cheapest Dedicated Servers if you are looking for a
                                    budget-friendly solution, or consider our Advanced-level Dedicated Servers if you
                                    plan to host a high-traffic website or application. We have options suitable for
                                    every need and budget.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <footer></footer>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
